name: Dermocybe Canaria "Canary Webcap"
description: Dermocybe Canaria, "Canary Webcap" is a rare, brightly colored species found in SE Australia and NZ, mycorrhizal with eucalypts. Cap and stem are bright yellow, cap to 80 mm, convex, umbonate, Stem often has a bulbous base, and veil remnants in a fugitive, fibrillose ring. Spore prints reveal yellowish rusty brown spores.
